# Review

Run this checklist before committing changes.

## Security
- [ ] No secrets, keys, or tokens in committed files
- [ ] No SQL injection, XSS, or command injection vectors
- [ ] Auth checks present on protected routes
- [ ] Sensitive data not logged or exposed in error messages

## Correctness
- [ ] Edge cases handled (empty input, nulls, boundary values)
- [ ] Error paths tested - failures don't silently corrupt state
- [ ] Types match across file boundaries (API contracts, shared interfaces)
- [ ] No leftover debug code, TODO placeholders, or template values

## Maintainability
- [ ] Changes are minimal - no unrelated refactors bundled in
- [ ] New abstractions justified by multiple use sites
- [ ] Comments explain *why*, not *what*
- [ ] Test coverage for new behavior
